Package: rpki
Type: Package
Title: A wrapper around the httr package to make it easier to access PKI-enabled services with R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("nbgallery", email = "nbgallery@github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: nbgallery [aut, cre]
Maintainer: nbgallery <nbgallery@github.com>
Description: A wrapper around the httr package to make it easier to access
    PKI-enabled services with R. Conceptually, rpki is very similar to the
    Ruby MyPKI package and Python pypki2 package, and is intended to use the
    same ~/.mypki configuration file.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1.9000
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0),
    httr (>= 1.2.1)
Imports:
    openssl (>= 0.9.6),
    getPass (>= 0.1-1),
    jsonlite (>= 1.3),
    tools (>= 3.3.0),
    stringr (>= 1.2.0)
URL: https://github.com/nbgallery/rpki
